pe%20the%20trajectory%20of%20the%20state%20for%20decades%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20mission%20drives%20him%2C%20especially%20since%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwes-moore-maryland-governor-election-patriotism-democrats-maga-trump-2022-10%5C%22%3Ehad%20never%20held%20elected%20office%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%20becoming%20governor.%20His%20path%2C%20should%20he%20succeed%2C%20is%20not%20an%20unfamiliar%20one%3A%20recent%20American%20political%20history%20is%20full%20of%20such%20figures%20who%20came%20to%20office%20as%20outsiders%2C%20adapted%20quickly%20to%20work%20with%20a%20legislature%2C%20and%20made%20things%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20brand%20%E2%80%94%20an%20outsider%20who%20gets%20things%20done%20%E2%80%94%20has%20long%20punched%20the%20tickets%20of%20presidential%20contenders%2C%20from%20Mitt%20Romney%20to%20Chris%20Christie.%20Should%20he%20succeed%2C%20Wes%20Moore%20could%20be%20next.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20an%20interview%20in%20the%20governor's%20office%20in%20late%20June%2C%20Moore%20told%20me%20that%20he%20wanted%20Marylanders%20to%20see%20that%20his%20administration%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bbold%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bstill%20be%20responsible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20we%20were%20able%20to%20get%20all%20of%20our%20bills%20passed%20with%20Republicans%2C%20I%20think%20was%20shocking%20to%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2044-year-old%20Democratic%20governor%20said%20of%20bipartisan%20cooperation%20in%20the%20decidedly%20blue%20state.%20%26quot%3BThey%20saw%20that%20we%20meant%20it%20when%20we%20said%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20make%20our%20case%20in%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20state.%20I%20think%20people%20saw%20that%20was%20legitimate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20the%20way%2C%20Moore%20spoke%20about%20the%20transition%20from%20campaigning%20to%20governing%2C%20gun%20violence%2C%20book%20bans%2C%20and%20his%20thoughts%20on%20what%20actually%20defines%20the%20Democratic%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'We're%20not%20demanding%20that%20other%20people%20do%20things'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20has%20long%20been%20floated%20by%20many%20Democrats%20as%20a%20future%20Senate%20or%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20with%20many%20seeing%20the%20governor%20as%20part%20of%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20leaders%20in%20a%20party%20that%20has%20often%20been%20criticized%20for%20failing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgerontocracy-united-states-government-red-white-gray-2022-9%5C%22%3Etransition%20political%20power%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20younger%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20national%20Republicans%20have%20largely%20been%20defined%20by%20their%20push%20for%20tax%20cuts%20and%20their%20opposition%20to%20abortion%20rights%2C%20national%20Democrats%20have%20sometimes%20been%20called%20out%20for%20not%20having%20a%20clear%20message%20for%20voters%20about%20their%20core%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%2C%20who%20was%20sworn%20into%20office%20in%20January%2C%20has%20his%20own%20answer%20for%20how%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20should%20pitch%20itself%20to%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20had%20to%20break%20it%20down%20in%20one%20word%2C%20it's%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BOn%20the%20national%20level%2C%20we%20have%20the%20biggest%20and%20most%20impactful%20bipartisan%20piece%20of%20infrastructure%20legislation%20that's%20ever%20passed.%20On%20the%20local%20side%2C%20I%20stood%20with%20President%20Biden%20during%20my%20first%20weeks%20of%20office%20and%20we%20announced%20that%20we%20were%20working%20together%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amtrak.com%2Ffdtunnel%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFrederick%20Douglass%20Tunnel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20going%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FWhiteHouse%2Fstatus%2F1622037291182039040%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproduce%3C%2Fa%3E%2030%2C000%20good%20paying%20jobs%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Maryland.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20speaking%20about%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20in%20Maryland%2C%20Moore%20leaned%20into%20a%20similar%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20work%20that%20we're%20doing%20here%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Maryland%2C%20it's%20results%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20talking%20about%20things%20and%20we're%20not%20demanding%20that%20other%20people%20do%20things.%20We're%20doing%20them%20ourselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'There's%20not%20a%20drop%20of%20entitlement%20in%20our%20team'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%2C%20who%20was%20elected%20with%20nearly%2065%25%20of%20the%20vote%20last%20November%20against%20then-GOP%20state%20Del.%20Dan%20Cox%2C%20ran%20on%20a%20platform%20of%20strengthening%20public%20education%2C%20expanding%20the%20state's%20earned%20income%20tax%20credit%2C%20enacting%20a%20service-year%20program%20for%20high%20school%20graduates%2C%20bolstering%20access%20to%20health%20care%2C%20and%20aiding%20the%20state's%20military%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20Moore%20saw%20the%20earned%20income%20tax%20credit%20created%20by%20the%20Maryland%20legislative%20in%202020%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmgaleg.maryland.gov%2F2023RS%2Ffnotes%2Fbil_0002%2Fsb0552.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emade%20permanent%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20also%20signing%20into%20law%20an%20eligibility%20expansion%20of%20the%20state's%20child-tax%20credit%20%E2%80%94%20part%20of%20his%20longstanding%20desire%20to%20end%20child%20poverty%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20governor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmgaleg.maryland.gov%2F2023RS%2Ffnotes%2Fbil_0001%2Fsb0551.pdf%5C%22%3Esigned%20into%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20service-year%20option%20that%20he%20had%20long%20championed.%20And%20he%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmgaleg.maryland.gov%2Fmgawebsite%2FLegislation%2FDetails%2Fsb0554%3Fys%3D2023RS%5C%22%3Eapproved%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20health-care%20reimbursement%20program%20for%20Maryland%20National%20Guard%20members%2C%20one%20that%20he%20hopes%20will%20be%20a%20first%20step%20to%20them%20having%20free%20health%20and%20dental%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224351%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wes%20Moore%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aefa5c94be880019f3a7c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222903%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMoore%20in%20his%20office%20at%20the%20Maryland%20State%20House%20in%20Annapolis.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Robinson%20Cha%CC%81vez%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20what%20was%20an%20early%20setback%2C%20the%20overwhelmingly%20Democratic%20legislature%20pared%20down%20the%20National%20Guard%20health%20care%20program.%20But%20Moore%20%E2%80%94%20who%20served%20as%20a%20captain%20and%20paratrooper%20in%20the%20US%20Army's%2082nd%20Airborne%20Division%20and%20was%20deployed%20to%20Afghanistan%20from%202005%20to%202006%20%E2%80%94%20was%20jubilant%20about%20the%20initial%20step%2C%20telling%20me%20that%20Maryland%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20state%20in%20the%20country%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20on%20the%20path%20to%20offering%20full%20health%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20was%20emphatic%20in%20stating%20that%20the%20administration%20that%20he%20assembled%20alongside%20Lt.%20Gov.%20Aruna%20Miller%20%E2%80%94%20a%20former%20state%20lawmaker%20with%20deep%20transportation%20policy%20acumen%20who%20knows%20the%20ropes%20in%20Annapolis%20%E2%80%94%20allowed%20for%20many%20of%20their%20proposals%20to%20become%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20a%20drop%20of%20entitlement%20in%20our%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20showed%20that%20you%20could%20both%20focus%20on%20representation%20and%20not%20compromise%20excellence.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20was%20an%20important%20component%20to%20what%20we've%20been%20able%20to%20get%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOn%20guns%20in%20public%20places%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20just%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20it's%20my%20right'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20brought%20up%20the%20issue%20of%20gun%20violence%2C%20Moore%20immediately%20pointed%20to%20a%20graphic%20that%20he%20saw%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.capitalgazette.com%2Fmaryland%2Fannapolis%2Fac-cn-capital-gazette-shooting-five-year-20230628-zjgg5lar45ea7iuiendhnt65am-story.html%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20Capital%20Gazette%3C%2Fa%3E%20displaying%20the%20number%20of%20mass%20shootings%20that%20have%20occurred%20in%20the%20US%20since%20that%20Annapolis-based%20newspaper%20suffered%20its%20own%20tragedy%20five%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2028%2C%202018%2C%20a%20gunman%2C%20Jarrod%20Ramos%2C%20stormed%20into%20the%20offices%20of%20the%20Gazette%2C%20killing%20five%20staff%20members%2C%20in%20what%20was%20one%20of%20the%20deadliest%20attacks%20on%20journalists%20in%20the%20country%20since%209%2F11.%20(He%20was%20found%20criminally%20responsible%20for%20the%20murders%20and%20in%20September%202021%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.capitalgazette.com%2Fnews%2Fac-cn-capital-gazette-shooting-sentence-tuesday-20210928-dqpmoiu6hjgylontchcvnnkv3u-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esentenced%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20five%20consecutive%20life%20sentences%20without%20the%20possibility%20of%20parole.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20graphic%20was%20a%20visual%20reminder%20of%20the%20274%20people%20who%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20public%20mass%20shootings%20beginning%20with%20the%20attacks%20in%20the%20Gazette%20newsroom%20through%20June%2026%3B%20it%20highlighted%20incidents%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpittsburgh-synagogue-shooting-how-it-unfolded-2018-10%5C%22%3E2018%20Tree%20of%20Life%20synagogue%20mass%20shooting%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Pittsburgh%2C%20Pennsylvania%2C%20and%20%