eric%20moisture%20that%20created%20a%20heat%20index.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Colin%20McCarthy%20from%20US%20Stormwatch%2C%20the%20Iran%20airport%20reported%20a%20heat%20index%20of%20152%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20(66.7%20degrees%20Celsius).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EPersian%20Gulf%20International%20Airport%20in%20Iran%20reported%20a%20heat%20index%20of%20152%C2%B0F%20(66.7%C2%B0C)%20today%20at%2012%3A30%20pm.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThose%20are%20intolerable%20conditions%20for%20human%2Fanimal%20life.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FR3RJ9pf4DC%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FR3RJ9pf4DC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Colin%20McCarthy%20(%40US_Stormwatch)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FUS_Stormwatch%2Fstatus%2F1680700765265072128%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2016%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPersian%20Gulf%20International%20Airport%20in%20Iran%20reported%20a%20heat%20index%20of%20152%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20(66.7%20degrees%20Celsius)%20today%20at%2012%3A30%20pm.%20Those%20are%20intolerable%20conditions%20for%20human%2Fanimal%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20tweet%20posted%20on%20July%2016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20calculate%20how%20hot%20or%20cold%20the%20weather%20feels%2C%20meteorologists%20use%20equations%20that%20factor%20in%20air%20temperature%20and%20other%20atmospheric%20variables.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20widely-used%20methods%20for%20estimating%20the%20impacts%20of%20hot%20weather%20is%20called%20the%20'heat%20index'%2C%20which%20combines%20air%20temperature%20and%20humidity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shocking%20temperature%20was%20seen%20in%20Iran%20after%20searing%20inland%20heat%20clashed%20with%20humid%20air%20flowing%20off%20the%20very%20warm%20waters%20of%20the%20Persian%20Gulf.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20mentioned%20by%20Mr%20McCarthy%2C%20the%20temperature%20at%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%20International%20Airport%20reached%2040%20Degrees%20Celsius%2C%20with%20a%20relative%20humidity%20of%2065%20per%20cent%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weather.gov%2Fwrh%2Ftimeseries%3Fsite%3DOIBP%26hours%3D72%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20NOAA%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20created%20an%20apparent%20temperature%20of%2066.7%20degrees%20Celsius.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExtreme%20heat%20can%20have%20devastating%20impact%20on%20humans.%20According%20to%20vaccine%20alliance%20GAVI%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20dehydration%20and%20if%20a%20person%20doesn't%20drink%20enough%20water%20to%20replace%20that%20lost%20through%20sweating%20and%20urination%2C%20the%20blood%20starts%20to%20thicken%2C%20making%20it%20more%20prone%20to%20clotting%2C%20which%20increases%20the%20risk%20of%20heart%20attack%20and%20stroke.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExposure%20to%20high%20temperature%20can%20also%20amplify%20existing%20health%20problems%2C%20making%20older%20people%20and%20those%20with%20chronic%20conditions%20at%20particularly%20high%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Bloomberg%20report%2C%20July%20is%20already%20on%20track%20to%20be%20the%20hottest%20ever%20year%2C%20with%2010%20of%20the%20hottest%20days%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimultaneous%20heat%20waves%20are%20suffocating%20the%20US%2C%20much%20of%20Europe%20and%20parts%20of%20Asia%2C%20while%20El%20Nino%20intensifies%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20and%20the%20Atlantic%20waters%20off%20Florida%20hit%20an%20unprecedented%2032.2%20degrees%20Celsius.%20China%20has%20already%20recorded%20its%20highest-ever%20temperature%20of%2052.2%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20Sanbo%20township.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Akshay%20Deoras%2C%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Reading's%20meteorology%20department%2C%20has%20warned%20of%20%26quot%3Bmore%20frequent%20and%20intense%26quot%3B%20extreme%20weather%20events%20if%20global%20temperatures%20continue%20to%20rise%20at%20th