20too%20worried%20about%20the%20Fed's%20policy.%20Krugman%20for%20one%2C%20said%20the%20US%20may%20escape%20a%20recession%20with%20inflation%20dropping%20and%20robust%20job%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffeds-mystical-inflation-target-illogical-joblessness-blackrock-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689598623000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f524d087ed0ee001e25d806%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ffeds-mystical-inflation-target-illogical-joblessness-blackrock-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThis%202%25%20is%20some%20magical%2C%20mystical%20perfection%20%E2%80%93%20it's%20illogical%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20BlackRock's%20chief%20investment%20officer%20Rick%20Rieder%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ztayeb%40businessinsider.com%20(Zahra%20Tayeb)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A19%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ffeds-mystical-inflation-target-illogical-joblessness-blackrock-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222023%20On%20Track%20To%20Be%20Hottest%20Year%20Ever%20Recorded%2C%20Say%20Experts%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20hottest%20June%20on%20record%20has%20been%20followed%20by%20an%20early%20July%20that%20now%20includes%2010%20of%20the%20hottest%20days%20in%20history.%20Simultaneous%20heat%20waves%20are%20suffocating%20the%20US%2C%20much%20of%20Europe%20and%20parts%20of%20Asia%2C%20while%20El%20Nino%20intensifies%20in%20the%20Pacific%20Ocean%20and%20the%20Atlantic%20waters%20off%20Florida%20hit%20an%20unprecedented%2090F%20(32.2C).%20It's%20already%20enough%20to%20put%202023%20on%20a%20likely%20trajectory%20to%20become%20the%20warmest%20year%20since%20record-keeping%20began%20in%20the%201800s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20October%202019%2C%20the%20research%20nonprofit%20Berkeley%20Earth%20has%20been%20analyzing%20each%20month's%20global%20temperatures%20and%20issuing%20predictions%20for%20the%20year's%20ultimate%20rank%20in%20terms%20of%20heat.%20Its%20latest%20analysis%2C%20published%20July%2011%2C%20found%20%26quot%3Ba%20fairly%20high%20chance%20-%20above%2080%25%20at%20this%20point%20-%20that%202023%20will%20be%20the%20warmest%20year%20on%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Zeke%20Hausfather%2C%20a%20Berkeley%20Earth%20climate%20scientist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearchers%20will%20finalize%20annual%20temperature%20rankings%20in%20January.%20To%20date%2C%20the%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%20is%20a%20tie%20between%202016%20and%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20longtime%20climate%20observers%2C%20the%20summer's%20breakneck%20pace%20of%20temperature%20records%20is%20a%20grim%20pattern%20long%20predicted%2C%20and%20one%20with%20little%20chance%20of%20breaking.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20expecting%20this%20for%2020%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Camille%20Parmesan%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Scientific%20Research%20and%20an%20Intergovernmental%20Panel%20on%20Climate%20Change%20report%20author.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20going%20to%20keep%20happening%20given%20that%20we're%20not%20reducing%20emissions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarth%20has%20already%20warmed%201.2C%20since%20the%20preindustrial%20era%20due%20to%20growing%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20This%20has%20resulted%20in%20a%20clear%20trend%3A%2022%20of%20the%20last%2023%20years%20were%20the%20hottest%20ever%2C%20according%20to%20NOAA.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20stop%20this%20trend%2C%20climate%20scientists%20have%20repeatedly%20warned%2C%20is%20for%20people%20to%20dramatically%20and%20immediately%20cut%20their%20climate%20pollutants%2C%20mainly%20through%20ditching%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHigh%20among%20the%20factors%20pushing%20this%20year's%20unparalleled%20heat%20trajectory%20is%20the%20aforementioned%20El%20Nino%2C%20the%20first%20in%20nearly%20four%20years.%20The%20Pacific%20basin%20covers%20one-third%20of%20the%20planet%20and%20is%20subject%20to%20the%20El%20Nino-Southern%20Oscillation%2C%20which%20ping-pongs%20the%20ocean's%20temperatures%20between%20cold%20and%20warm%20phases.%20This%20year%20started%20off%20in%20the%20La%20Nina%20phase%2C%20officially%20switching%20to%20El%20Nino%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20we%20have%20an%20El%20Nino%20event%2C%20we%20get%20a%20small%20peek%20into%20the%20future.%20This%20is%20what%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20new%20normal%20for%20the%20climate%20in%205%20to%2010%20years%20if%20our%20emissions%20keep%20at%20current%20levels%20and%20don't%20decrease%20rapidly%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Hausfather%20says.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20slightly%20higher%20than%20normal%20temperatures%20this%20year%20and%20next%2C%20but%20long-term%20climate%20change%20is%20going%20to%20quickly%20push%20the%20planet%20to%20these%20levels%20of%20heat%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorsening%20climate%20change%20is%20driving%20up%20the%20frequency%20and%20intensity%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20and%20this%20summer%20is%20no%20exception.%20Heat%20waves%20have%20plagued%20Japan%2C%20India%20and%20the%20US%2C%20which%20has%20also%20struggled%20with%20devastating%20flooding%20in%20the%20Northeast.%20Drought%20now%20grips%20Europe%2C%20following%20record%20spring%20heat%20in%20the%20Mediterranean.%20Canada%20is%20wrestling%20with%20out%20of%20control%20wildfires%2C%20which%20have%20unleashed%20waves%20of%20dangerous%20smoke%20on%20millions%20of%20people%20across%20North%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEl%20Ninos%20are%20just%20another%20type%20of%20extreme%20event%20that%20have%20also%20gotten%20stronger%20in%20recent%20decades%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20%26quot%3BSince%201950%2C%20El%20Ninos%20have%20been%20significantly%20stronger%20than%20any%20time%20from%201400%20to%201950%2C%26quot%3B%20Parmesan%20says%2C%20citing%20a%202021%20IPCC%20report%20she%20helped%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20had%20an%20El%20Nino%20event%20at%20this%20level%20of%20global%20warming%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brown%20University's%20climate%20scientist%2C%20Kim%20Cobb.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20that's%20an%20obvious%20statement%20but%20I%20think%20it%20still%20needs%20to%20be%20said.%26quot%3B%20The%20implication%20is%20we%20don't%20really%20know%20what's%20in%20store%2C%20Cobb%20warns%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20El%20Nino%20is%20only%20just%20beginning%20%26quot%3Band%20it's%20forecast%20to%20get%20quite%20a%20bit%20stronger.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBerkeley%20Earth's%20estimated%20odds%20for%202023%20as%20the%20hottest%20year%20increased%20as%20the%20year%20went%20on%3B%20if%20the%20El%20Nino%20persists%20and%20intensifies%2C%202024%20could%20be%20hotter.%20After%20January%2C%20the%20group%20noted%20that%202023%20had%20a%2014%25%20chance%20of%20being%20the%20hottest%20year%3B%20by%20the%20end%20of%20May%2C%20it%20had%20risen%20to%2054%25.%20Then%20came%20a%20stunningly%20hot%20June.%20Declared%20the%20warmest%20on%20record%20by%20Berkeley%20Earth%2C%20the%20US%20National%20Centers%20for%20Environmental%20Information%20and%20the%20European%20Union's%20Copernicus%20Climate%20Change%20Service%2C%20it%20beat%20out%20by%20a%20significant%20margin%20a%20previous%20set%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20disasters%20are%20expected%20to%20plague%20communities%20as%20the%20year%20continues%2C%20amid%20an%20especially%20hot%20summer%20and%20fall.%20Or%20as%20Zeke%20Hausfather%20puts%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20bad%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689598260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvim