25392.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAlia%20Bhatt%20has%20been%20added%20to%20YRF's%20spy%20universe%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20play%20a%20gender-free%20superhero%20no%20less%20glamorous%20and%20sexy%20than%20Salman%20and%20SRK%20in%20the%20upcoming%20film.%20Director%20Aditya%20Chopra%20wants%20to%20break%20the%20stereotypical%20image%20of%20female%20heroes%20and%20hence%20wants%20Alia%20to%20play%20a%20makeup-free%20no-vanity%20superhero%20in%20a%20mission%20to%20save%20the%20world.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwill-shah-rukh-khan-and-salman-khan-make-an-appearance-in-alia-bhatts-superhero-film-in-yrfs-spy-universe-heres-what-we-know-%2Farticleshow%2F101825392.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Japanese%20Company%20Bans%20Late-Night%20Work.%20A%20Baby%20Boom%20Soon%20Follows%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWhen%20Masahiro%20Okafuji%20became%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Itochu%20Corp.%20in%202010%2C%20he%20made%20improving%20productivity%20a%20top%20priority%20so%20the%20company%20could%20compete%20against%20bigger%20rivals%20in%20Japan.%20His%20approach%20was%20counterintuitive.%20Working%20in%20the%20office%20after%208%20p.m.%20would%20be%20banned%2C%20and%20there%20would%20be%20no%20more%20overtime-with%20rare%20exceptions.%20Security%20guards%20and%20human%20resources%20staff%20would%20scout%20Itochu's%20office%20building%20in%20Tokyo%2C%20telling%20people%20to%20go%20home.%20Those%20clinging%20to%20their%20desk%20were%20told%20to%20come%20in%20early%20the%20next%20day%20to%20get%20their%20work%20done-and%20get%20paid%20extra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tough%20love%20worked.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20the%20company-whose%20businesses%20range%20from%20the%20FamilyMart%20convenience%20store%20chain%20to%20metals%20trading-reported%20a%20more%20than%20fivefold%20jump%20in%20profit%20per%20employee%20from%202010%20to%202021%20as%20surging%20commodities%20prices%20and%20a%20weak%20yen%20buoyed%20its%20bottom%20line.%20What%20also%20changed%2C%20to%20the%20surprise%20of%20Itochu's%20management%2C%20is%20that%20more%20female%20employees%20took%20maternity%20leave%2C%20had%20kids%20and%20came%20back%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20set%20out%20to%20boost%20productivity%20but%20had%20no%20idea%20it%20would%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20birthrate%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Fumihiko%20Kobayashi%2C%20Itochu's%20executive%20vice%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trading%20house%20has%20emerged%20as%20an%20unlikely%20trailblazer%20in%20bucking%20a%20falling%20birthrate%20trend%20that%20Japan's%20government%20and%20others%20around%20the%20world%20have%20tried%20hard%20to%20reverse%2C%20without%20much%20success.%20Itochu%20saw%20the%20fertility%20rate%20among%20full-time%20employees%20double%20in%20the%20years%20since%20Okafuji%20became%20CEO%2C%20reaching%20almost%20two%20children%20per%20female%20employee%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%20ended%20March%2031%2C%202022-far%20exceeding%20Japan's%20current%20national%20rate%20of%20about%201.3.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20birthrate%20spike%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20Itochu%20board%20member%20Atsuko%20Muraki%2C%20who%20previously%20served%20as%20director%20of%20equal%20employment%20and%20child%20welfare%20at%20Japan's%20Ministry%20of%20Health%2C%20Labour%20and%20Welfare.%20She%20encouraged%20the%20company%20to%20make%20the%20trend-defying%20numbers%20public%20last%20year%2C%20seeking%20to%20send%20the%20social%20message%20that%2C%20for%20women%2C%20raising%20kids%20and%20having%20a%20career%20don't%20have%20to%20come%20at%20each%20other's%20expense.%20Mixed%20reactions%20followed.%20Some%20criticized%20Itochu%20for%20meddling%20in%20employees'%20lives%20and%20being%20insensitive%20to%20those%20with%20reproductive%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapan%20has%20long%20been%20known%20for%20a%20work%20culture%20in%20which%20grueling%20hours%20at%20the%20office-often%20followed%20by%20evenings%20spent%20eating%20and%20drinking%20with%20work%20colleagues-make%20having%20a%20family%20challenging%2C%20especially%20for%20female%20workers.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20many%20women%20exit%20the%20workforce%20to%20care%20for%20kids.%20Itochu's%20night%20work%20ban%20eased%20some%20of%20that%20pressure.%20And%20after%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%2C%20employees%20were%20granted%20the%20option%20to%20work%20from%20home%20two%20days%20a%20week.%20The%20company%20went%20further%20last%20year%2C%20when%20it%20cut%20core%20office%20hours%20from%20eight%20to%20six%2C%20so%20people%20can%20punch%20out%20as%20early%20as%203%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20while%20getting%20pregnant%20might%20effectively%20mark%20the%20end%20of%20a%20woman's%20career%20at%20lots%20of%20other%20Japanese%20businesses%2C%20many%20female%20employees%20at%20Itochu%20returned%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20curtailed%20working%20hours%20and%20a%20day-care%20center%20the%20company%20set%20up%20near%20its%20office%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20juggle%20jobs%20and%20caring%20for%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EItochu's%20experience%20could%20offer%20some%20particularly%20important%20lessons%20for%20Japan%20and%20its%20neighbors%20in%20East%20Asia%20battling%20falling%20fertility%20rates.%20Japanese%20Prime%20Minister%20Fumio%20Kishida%20is%20seeking%20to%20halt%20an%20accelerating%20birth%20decline%20that%20he%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20threatens%20to%20create%20an%2011%20million%20worker%20shortfall%20by%202040%20and%20lead%20to%20a%20collapse%20in%20the%20nation's%20pension%20and%20health-care%20system.%20A%20new%20agency%20for%20children%20and%20families%20was%20created%20in%20April%20to%20tackle%20these%20challenges%2C%20while%20in%20June%20Kishida%20pledged%20%2425%20billion%20in%20new%20policies%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20have%20more%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%20Japan%2C%20falling%20fertility%20rates%20risk%20taking%20the%20steam%20out%20of%20Asia's%20economic%20powerhouses.%20South%20Korea%20has%20had%20the%20world's%20lowest%20birthrate%20for%20years%2C%20dipping%20to%200.78%20in%202022.%20The%20proportion%20of%20women%20age%2025%20to%2039%20dropping%20out%20of%20the%20workforce%20there%20is%20also%20the%20highest%20among%20developed%20nations%2C%20believed%20to%20stem%20in%20part%20from%20a%20lack%20of%20child%20care-another%20driver%20of%20low%20fertility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22o9j5fdt8%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fo9j5fdt8_birthrate-at-itochu-corp-graph-bloomberg_625x300_17_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20financial%20strain%20and%20lack%20of%20child%20support%20have%20also%20led%20China's%20population%20to%20shrink%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20six%20decades%2C%20handing%20the%20crown%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20populous%20country%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20secret%20that%20a%20punishing%2C%20unsupportive%20corporate%20culture%20across%20these%20Asian%20economies%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20women's%20willingness%20to%20have%20children.%20Many%20working%20in%20China's%20tech%20industry%20lament%20an%20overtime%20culture%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B996%26quot%3B-working%20from%209%20a.m.%20to%209%20p.m.%20for%20six%20days%20a%20week.%20Jack%20Ma%2C%20founder%20of%20Alibaba%20Group%20Holding%20Ltd.%2C%20drew%20widespread%20criticism%20in%202019%20for%20calling%20%26quot%3B996%26quot%3B%20a%20blessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20Chinese%20company%20recently%20sought%20to%20ease%20that%20toxic%20work%20culture.%20In%20June%20online%20travel%20agency%20Trip.com%20Group%20Ltd.%20said%20it%20would%20offer%20annual%2010%2C000-yuan%20(%241%2C379)%20child-care%20subsidies%20to%20employees%20for%20every%20newborn%20child%20through%20the%20age%20of%205%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20options%20to%20work%20from%20home%20and%20assisted-reproduction%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20trading%20houses%20such%20as%20Itochu%20have%20underpinned%20Japan's%20postwar%20economic%20miracle%2C%20they%20also%20embody%20the%20nation's%20corporate%20culture%20characterized%20by%20male%20dominance%2C%20long%20working%20hours%20and%20pressure%20to%20join%20drinking%20parties%20with%20bosses%20and%20clients%20after%20work.%20Few%20expected%20major%20companies%20like%20Itochu%2C%20Mitsui%2C%20Mitsubishi%20or%20Sumitomo%20to%20break%20away%20from%20the%20decades-old%20ethos%20of%20extreme%20dedication%20to%20work%20and%20become%20a%20pioneer%20in%20the%20push%20for%20better%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20Anna%20Furuya%20returned%20from%20maternity%20leave%20in%202013%20to%20her%20job%20at%20the%20time%20in%20Itochu's%20textile%20division%2C%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20company's%20working-hour%20reforms%2C%20she%20felt%20like%20an%20outlier%20whenever%20she%20left%20for%20home%20earlier%20than%20her%20colleagues.%20%26quot%3BThe%20change%20hadn't%20sunk%20in%20yet%2C%20so%20I%20was%20a%20minority%20using%20it%20and%20felt%20guilty%20to%20leave%20early%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20the%2038-year-old%2C%20who%20these%20days%20works%20in%20Itochu's%20corporate%20division%2C%20says%20she's%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20happy%26quot%3B%20with%20her%20life%20as%20a%20working%20mother.%20Furuya%20sometimes%20starts%20her%20day%20in%20the%20office%20at%20about%206%3A30%20a.m.%20and%20leaves%20around%204%20p.m.%20She%20can%20then%20watch%20her%209-year-old%20son%20do%20his%20homework%20while%20cooking%20dinner.%20%26quot%3BFor%20people%20like%20me%20who%20are%20raising%20kids%2C%20it's%20really%20necessary%20to%20shift%20your%20life%20to%20earlier%20in%20the%20morning%20to%20be%20efficient%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20Japanese%20enterprises%20have%20taken%20note.%20Mitsui%20Sumitomo%20Insurance%20Co.%20said%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20starting%20this%20month%20it%20would%20give%20as%20much%20as%20100%2C000%20yen%20(%24700)%20to%20employees%20who%20assume%20some%20of%20the%20workload%20from%20colleagues%20on%20child-care%20leave.%20And%20Recruit%20Holdings%20Co.%2C%20the%20Japanese%20parent%20of%20job%20search%20and%20review%20sites%20Indeed.com%20and%20Glassdoor%2C%20allows%20employees%20to%20work%20from%20home%20most%20of%20the%20time%20and%20offers%20extra%20days%20off%20on%20top%20of%20statutory%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBig%20companies%20are%20generally%20more%20active%20in%20introducing%20work%20flexibility%20than%20smaller%20ones.%20Almost%20a%20third%20of%20large%20companies%20in%20Japan%20with%20more%20than%201%2C000%20employees%20offer%20flexible%20work%20hours%2C%20compared%20with%20fewer%20than%2010%25%20of%20those%20with%20no%20more%20than%20100%20people%2C%20government%20data%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20some%20question%20whether%20Itochu's%20success%20can%20be%20replicated%20more%20broadly.%20Child-rearing%20requires%20both%20money%20and%20time.%20Trading%20houses%20offer%20some%20of%20Japan's%20most%20well-paid%20jobs.%20The%20average%20annual%20income%20for%20someone%20working%20at%20Itochu%20in%202023%2C%2017.3%20million%20yen%2C%20is%20about%20four%20times%20the%20national%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20reason%20for%20the%20birthrate%20drop%20is%20that%20people%20with%20low%20economic%20status%20don't%20have%20financial%20means%20to%20have%20a%20family%20or%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Yasuko%20Hassall%20Kobayashi%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20Asian%20studies%20at%20Ritsumeikan%20University.%20%26quot%3BItochu%20represents%20wealthy%20people%20in%20Japan.%20Employees%20and%20their%20partners%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20high%20earners%20who%20can%20afford%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20so-called%20shosha%20man%20stereotype%20of%20male%20corporate%20elites%20no%20longer%20fits%20Itochu's%20workforce.%20The%20company%20says%20the%20flexibility%20and%20support%20it%20offers%20have%20attracted%20more%20women%20to%20join%20and%20fill%20mission-critical%20positions.%20Male%20employees%20also%20appear%20to%20be%20more%20involved%20with%20their%20families-half%20of%20them%20have%20taken%20paternity%20leave%2C%20compared%20with%2014%25%20of%20male%20workers%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20feel%20guilty%20about%20leaving%20early%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Furuya%2C%20the%20working%20mom%20at%20Itochu%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20it%20applies%20to%20everyone%2C%20not%20just%20mothers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689588420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fanbutrm8_itochu-corp-bloomberg_625x300_17_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fa-japanese-company-bans-late-night-work-a-baby-boom-soon-follows-4214551%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20Masahiro%20Okafuji%20became%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20Itochu%20Corp.%20in%202010%2C%20he%20made%20improving%20productivity%20a%20top%20priority%20so%20the%20company%20could%20compete%20against%20bigger%20rivals%20in%20Japan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fa-japanese-company-bans-late-night-work-a-baby-boom-soon-follows-4214551%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fa-japanese-company-bans-late-night-work-a-baby-boom-soon-follows-4214551%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fa-japanese-company-bans-late-night-work-a-baby-boom-soon-follows-4214551%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gilbert%20Deya%3A%20Keny