g%20bans).%20Still%2C%20if%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20need%20to%20impose%20a%20ban%2C%20they%20must%20follow%20the%20due%20process%20of%20law%20and%20elected%20representatives%20should%20be%20able%20to%20explain%20to%20their%20voters%20the%20reasons%20for%20such%20bans.%20Internet%20ban%20is%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20dangers%20in%20building%20trust%20among%20the%20public%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nwakanma%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fprimacy-of-right-to-life-says-india-at-g20-talks-on-internet-shutdowns%2Farticleshow%2F101805891.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20the%20dubious%20distinction%20of%20being%20the%20internet%20shutdown%20capital%20of%20the%20world.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findia-remains-internet-shutdown-capital-of-the-world-for-fifth-year-running-report%5C%22%3Eresearch%20by%20Access%20Now%20has%20shown%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20since%202016%2C%20India%20has%20accounted%20for%20approximately%2058%25%20of%20all%20shutdowns%20documented%20in%20the%20Shutdown%20Tracker%20Optimization%20Project%20(STOP%20database).%20India%20is%20the%20only%20G20%20country%20that%20has%20imposed%20an%20internet%20shutdown%20more%20than%20twice.%20Russia%20and%20Brazil%20are%20the%20other%20two%20courtiers%20that%20enforced%20two%20and%20one%20internet%20shutdowns%20respectively%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20recently%2C%20in%20Manipur%20the%20government%20has%20indefinitely%20suspended%20internet%20services%20after%20ethnic%20violence%20broke%20out%20on%20May%203.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20hearing%20pleas%20against%20this%20suspension.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20query%20on%20the%20frequent%20internet%20bans%20in%20India%2C%20former%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20chief%20and%20member%20of%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20Rajiv%20Jain%20reportedly%20stated%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20is%20sometimes%20in%20conflict%20with%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20right%20to%20privacy.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20there%20is%20a%20threat%20to%20life%20of%20a%20large%20group%20of%20people%20or%20in%20a%20large%20geographical%20area%2C%20primacy%20has%20to%20be%20given%20to%20Right%20to%20Life%20as%20the%20state%20acts%20as%20repository%20of%20all%20the%20rights%20and%20takes%20a%20call%20on%20temporary%20suspension%20of%20Internet%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689579653000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F01%2F07131244%2F2807100863_6b4b73964f_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-frequent-internet-shutdowns-discussed-at-g20-meeting%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Responding%20to%20a%20query%20on%20the%20frequent%20internet%20bans%20in%20India%2C%20former%20Intelligence%20Bureau%20chief%20and%20member%20of%20National%20Human%20Rights%20Commission%20Rajiv%20Jain%20reportedly%20stated%20that%20the%20right%20to%20life%20is%20sometimes%20in%20conflict%20with%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20right%20to%20privacy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A46%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-frequent-internet-shutdowns-discussed-at-g20-meeting%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20Priyanka%20To%20Kate%2C%20The%20Best-Dressed%20Celebrities%20At%20Wimbledon%202023%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%202023%20Wimbledon%20Championships%20have%20come%20to%20an%20end%20with%20Carlos%20Alcaraz%20winning%20the%20Wimbledon%20men's%20final%2C%20while%20Marketa%20Vondrousova%20won%20the%20Wimbledon%20women's%20singles%20championship.%20Right%20from%20the%20very%20start%2C%20the%20championship%20had%20been%20a%20stylish%20affair%20with%20celebrities%20and%20royals%20making%20t